    <comment>Update to the 1.65.0 packaging with a security re-vendor of the bundled
Go dependencies (no upstream source changes; tarball rebuilt from the
v1.65.0 tag with updated go.mod/vendor):

- golang.org/x/net 0.33.0 -&gt; 0.55.0: CVE-2025-22870, CVE-2025-22872,
  CVE-2025-47911, CVE-2025-58190, CVE-2026-33814, CVE-2026-39821,
  CVE-2026-25680, CVE-2026-25681, CVE-2026-27136, CVE-2026-42502,
  CVE-2026-42506 (bsc#1238699 bsc#1241838 bsc#1251495 bsc#1251689
  bsc#1265799 bsc#1266639 bsc#1267176)
- golang.org/x/crypto 0.31.0 -&gt; 0.52.0: thirteen ssh CVEs
  (bsc#1266179)
- google.golang.org/grpc 1.65.0 -&gt; 1.79.3: CVE-2026-33186 (bsc#1260295)
- github.com/moby/spdystream 0.4.0 -&gt; 0.5.1: CVE-2026-35469
  (bsc#1262269; vendored but not linked into any shipped binary,
  verified via go version -m on the built RPMs — bumped regardless)
- github.com/ulikunitz/xz 0.5.12 -&gt; 0.5.15: CVE-2025-58058 (bsc#1248946)
- github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v3 3.0.3 -&gt; 3.0.5: CVE-2026-34986
  (bsc#1262952)

Requires Go &gt;= 1.25 (x/net 0.55 directive). Also adds a tests
subpackage: the upstream e2e ginkgo suite as a single static binary
(kubevirt*-tests precedent), fixtures excluded.</comment>
